"v. 牵连，卷入纠纷 【英】 v. 牵连, 卷入纠纷(to involve in conflict or difficulties) 【记】 em+broil(争吵)→进 入争吵→牵连，broil 本身是一个单词, 意为'争吵, 对骂' 【例】 She embroiled herself in their argument. v. 使牵连入(争论、斗争或敌对行动); 使陷入(混淆或混乱) 【根】broil(n /v 争吵)em进入, broil = boil沸水－使陷入(混淆或混乱) 【记】em + broil 烧烤，争吵 → 陷入纠纷；音：被绕，被绕进去了→卷入纠纷 【相关】broil 烧烤，争吵，roil 煽动, 激怒 embroil (v.)  c.1600, ""throw into disorder,"" from French embrouillier (cognate of Italian imbrogliare), from en- ""in"" (see en- (1)) + brouiller ""confuse,"" from Old French brooillier (see broil (v.2)). Sense of ""involve in a quarrel"" is first attested c.1610. Related: Embroiled; embroiling."
